	)
	(text_box "Bring ~{SYNC} low to reset the digital block inside the ADC. This can be used to synchronize multiple AD7770s (that are driven off the same clock) so that they generate data at the same time.\nThis pin is internally synchronized with the MCLK and used to generate the INTERNAL_SYNC signal.\nNote that this usage of the pin seems to be discouraged by the datasheet -- they recommend routing the SYNC_OUT of the master ADC to the other ADCs' ~{SYNC_IN} Pins, rather than routing one signal to all the ~{START} pins. However, I'm not really sure why this is and don't see a reason this is the case, as it would demand an extra card pin when one is otherwise not needed. TBD whether this has any bad effects... (aside from the possibility of different ADCs being 1 MCLK cycle off which we do not care about)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 302.26 123.19 0)
		(size 59.69 34.29)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "569aed76-2370-41ec-a2dd-0b5102a81047")
	)
	(text_box "Auxillary analog input, to secondary SAR ADC. Unused for now but broken out to test points and given a weak pulldown to prevent the inputs from floating."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
